msContents.summary: Copy of the Shāhnāmah with 119 miniatures. A list of rulers and the length of their rule is pasted in before the text begins (f. 1v).

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: 539 leaves : 435 x 275 (315 x 195) mm bound to 450 x 290 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: After the first opening, pages generally laid out in 25 lines per page in 4 columns with gold double rules between each column; border-ruled and page-opening frame-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Dual page floriate illuminated first opening in gold, red, and blue with 5 lines of text on cloudbands (f. 1v-2r). Second illuminated header in the same colors (f. 273v). Floriate illuminated panels in gold red and blue across two columns indicate text divisions and appear numerously throughout the manuscript. 119 vividly colored miniatures, mostly half-page size (f. 19v, 23v, 27r, 42r, 45v, 52r, 55v, 57r-57v, 73v, 76r, 77v, 85r, 90r, 95r, 98r, 107r, 122r, 124v, 127v-128r, 132r, 138r, 144r, 146v, 148r, 154r, 156r, 169v, 174r, 179v-180r, 183v, 185r, 188r, 190v, 195v, 201v, 205r-205v, 215v, 217r, 227r-231v [a set of battle images], 235r-235v, 246v, 248v, 253r, 260r, 263v, 265r, 267v, 271v, 272r, 276r, 278v, 280v, 290r, 297r, 299r-299v, 300v, 304r, 306v, 311v, 316r, 318r, 320v, 322r, 324r, 329r, 333v, 336r, 339r, 340r, 342r, 328r, 354r, 355r, 356v, 358v, 363r, 365v, 367r, 371v, 376v, 388r, 395v, 399v, 420v, 431r, 435v, 437r, 441v, 454v, 463r, 473r, 477v, 481r, 484v, 487r, 493r, 499r, 500r, 503r, 507v, 511v, 526v, 530v, 533v). In many of the images, the king resembles Fatḥ-ʻAlī Shāh of the Qajar dynasty.

binding.p: Bound in dark brown leather over pasteboard with red leather doublure.

origin.p: The item is undated, but likely produced in the first half of the 19th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Anne Baker Lewis in 1933.
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.
